ARCHITECTURE.md
     1вҶ’# Architecture
     3вҶ’> Document is a work in progress!
     4вҶ’
     5вҶ’вҢҳK is born from a simple constraint: can you write a combobox with filtering and sorting using the [compound component](https://kentcdodds.com/blog/compound-components-with-react-hooks) approach? We didn't want to render items manually from an array:
     6вҶ’
     7вҶ’```tsx
     8вҶ’// No
     9вҶ’<>
    10вҶ’  {items.map((item) => {
    11вҶ’    return <div>{item}</div>
    12вҶ’  })}
    13вҶ’</>
    14вҶ’```
    15вҶ’
    16вҶ’We didn't want to provide a render prop:
    17вҶ’
    18вҶ’```tsx
    19вҶ’// No
    20вҶ’onItemRender={({ item }) => {
    21вҶ’  return <div>{item}</div>
    22вҶ’}}
    23вҶ’```
    24вҶ’
    25вҶ’Instead, we wanted to render components:
    26вҶ’
    27вҶ’```tsx
    28вҶ’// Yes
    29вҶ’<Item>My item</Item>
    30вҶ’```
    31вҶ’
    32вҶ’Especially, we wanted full component composition:
    33вҶ’
    34вҶ’```tsx
    35вҶ’// YES
    36вҶ’<>
    37вҶ’  <BlogItems />
    38вҶ’  {staticItems}
    39вҶ’</>
    40вҶ’```
    41вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    46вҶ’## Approach
    48вҶ’вҢҳK always keeps every item and group rendered in the React tree. Each item and group adds or removes itself from the DOM based on the search input. The DOM is authoritative.В Item selection order is based on the DOM order, which is based on the React render order, which the consumer provides.
    49вҶ’
    50вҶ’### Discarded approach
    52вҶ’We did not use `React.Children` iteration because it will not support component composition. There is no way to "peek inside" the items contained within `<BlogItems />`, so those items cannot be filtered.
    53вҶ’
    54вҶ’We did not use an object-based data array for each item, like `{ name: "Logout", action: () => logout() }` because this is strict and limiting. In reality, the interface of those objects grows with edge-cases, like `image`, `detailedSubTitle`, `hideWhenRootSearch`, etc. We prefer that you have full control of item rendering, including icons, keyboard shortcuts, and styling. Don't want an item shown? Don't render it. Only want to show an item under condition xyz? Render it.
    55вҶ’
    56вҶ’We did not use a render prop because they are an inelegant pattern and quickly fall to long, centralised if-else logic chains. For example, if you want a fancy sparkle rainbow item, you need a new if statement to render that item specially.
    57вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    60вҶ’## Example
    62вҶ’```tsx
    63вҶ’<Input value="b" />
    64вҶ’<List>
    65вҶ’  <Item>A</Item>
    66вҶ’  <Item>B</Item>
    67вҶ’</List>
    68вҶ’```
    69вҶ’
    70вҶ’The "A" item should not be shown! But we cannot remove it from the React tree, because the user controls it. In most cases, this is easy because the rendered items is sourced from a backing data array:
    71вҶ’
    72вҶ’```tsx
    73вҶ’<>
    74вҶ’  {['A', 'B'].map((item) => {
    75вҶ’    if (matches(item, search)) {
    76вҶ’      return <Item>{item}</Item>
    77вҶ’    }
    78вҶ’  })}
    79вҶ’</>
    80вҶ’```
    81вҶ’
    82вҶ’But in our case, the item will remain in the React tree and just be removed from the DOM:
    83вҶ’
    84вҶ’```tsx
    85вҶ’<List>
    86вҶ’  {/* returns `null`, no DOM created */}
    87вҶ’  <Item>A</Item>
    88вҶ’  <Item>B</Item>
    89вҶ’</List>
    90вҶ’```
    91вҶ’
    92вҶ’## Performance
    94вҶ’This is more expensive memory wise, because if there are 2,000 items but the list is filtered to only 2 items, we still allocate memory for 2,000 instances of the Item component. But it's our only option! Thankfully we can still keep the DOM size to 2 items.
    95вҶ’
    96вҶ’## Groups
    98вҶ’Item mount informs both the root and the parent group, which keeps track of items within it. Each group informs the root.
README.md
     5вҶ’# вҢҳK
     7вҶ’вҢҳK is a command menu React component that can also be used as an accessible combobox. You render items, it filters and sorts them automatically. вҢҳK supports a fully composable API <sup><sup>[How?](/ARCHITECTURE.md)</sup></sup>, so you can wrap items in other components or even as static JSX.
     8вҶ’
     9вҶ’## Install
    11вҶ’```bash
    12вҶ’pnpm install cmdk
    13вҶ’```
    14вҶ’
    15вҶ’## Use
    17вҶ’```tsx
    18вҶ’import { Command } from 'cmdk'
    19вҶ’
    20вҶ’const CommandMenu = () => {
    21вҶ’  return (
    22вҶ’    <Command label="Command Menu">
    23вҶ’      <Command.Input />
    24вҶ’      <Command.List>
    25вҶ’        <Command.Empty>No results found.</Command.Empty>
    26вҶ’
    27вҶ’        <Command.Group heading="Letters">
    28вҶ’          <Command.Item>a</Command.Item>
    29вҶ’          <Command.Item>b</Command.Item>
    30вҶ’          <Command.Separator />
    31вҶ’          <Command.Item>c</Command.Item>
    32вҶ’        </Command.Group>
    33вҶ’
    34вҶ’        <Command.Item>Apple</Command.Item>
    35вҶ’      </Command.List>
    36вҶ’    </Command>
    37вҶ’  )
    38вҶ’}
    39вҶ’```
    40вҶ’
    41вҶ’Or in a dialog:
    42вҶ’
    43вҶ’```tsx
    44вҶ’import { Command } from 'cmdk'
    45вҶ’
    46вҶ’const CommandMenu = () => {
    47вҶ’  const [open, setOpen] = React.useState(false)
    48вҶ’
    49вҶ’  // Toggle the menu when вҢҳK is pressed
    50вҶ’  React.useEffect(() => {
    51вҶ’    const down = (e) => {
    52вҶ’      if (e.key === 'k' && (e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey)) {
    53вҶ’        e.preventDefault()
    54вҶ’        setOpen((open) => !open)
    55вҶ’      }
    56вҶ’    }
    57вҶ’
    58вҶ’    document.addEventListener('keydown', down)
    59вҶ’    return () => document.removeEventListener('keydown', down)
    60вҶ’  }, [])
    61вҶ’
    62вҶ’  return (
    63вҶ’    <Command.Dialog open={open} onOpenChange={setOpen} label="Global Command Menu">
    64вҶ’      <Command.Input />
    65вҶ’      <Command.List>
    66вҶ’        <Command.Empty>No results found.</Command.Empty>
    67вҶ’
    68вҶ’        <Command.Group heading="Letters">
    69вҶ’          <Command.Item>a</Command.Item>
    70вҶ’          <Command.Item>b</Command.Item>
    71вҶ’          <Command.Separator />
    72вҶ’          <Command.Item>c</Command.Item>
    73вҶ’        </Command.Group>
    74вҶ’
    75вҶ’        <Command.Item>Apple</Command.Item>
    76вҶ’      </Command.List>
    77вҶ’    </Command.Dialog>
    78вҶ’  )
    79вҶ’}
    80вҶ’```
    81вҶ’
    82вҶ’## Parts and styling
    84вҶ’All parts forward props, including `ref`, to an appropriate element. Each part has a specific data-attribute (starting with `cmdk-`) that can be used for styling.
    85вҶ’
    86вҶ’### Command `[cmdk-root]`
    88вҶ’Render this to show the command menu inline, or use [Dialog](#dialog-cmdk-dialog-cmdk-overlay) to render in a elevated context. Can be controlled with the `value` and `onValueChange` props.
    89вҶ’
    90вҶ’> **Note**
    91вҶ’>
    92вҶ’> Values are always trimmed with the [trim()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String/trim) method.
    93вҶ’
    94вҶ’```tsx
    95вҶ’const [value, setValue] = React.useState('apple')
    96вҶ’
    97вҶ’return (
    98вҶ’  <Command value={value} onValueChange={setValue}>
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   153вҶ’### Dialog `[cmdk-dialog]` `[cmdk-overlay]`
   155вҶ’Props are forwarded to [Command](#command-cmdk-root). Composes Radix UI's Dialog component. The overlay is always rendered. See the [Radix Documentation](https://www.radix-ui.com/docs/primitives/components/dialog) for more information. Can be controlled with the `open` and `onOpenChange` props.
   156вҶ’
   157вҶ’```tsx
   158вҶ’const [open, setOpen] = React.useState(false)
   159вҶ’
   160вҶ’return (
   161вҶ’  <Command.Dialog open={open} onOpenChange={setOpen}>
   162вҶ’    ...
   163вҶ’  </Command.Dialog>
   164вҶ’)
   165вҶ’```
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   180вҶ’### Input `[cmdk-input]`
   182вҶ’All props are forwarded to the underlying `input` element. Can be controlled with the `value` and `onValueChange` props.
   183вҶ’
   184вҶ’```tsx
   185вҶ’const [search, setSearch] = React.useState('')
   186вҶ’
   187вҶ’return <Command.Input value={search} onValueChange={setSearch} />
   188вҶ’```
   189вҶ’
   190вҶ’### List `[cmdk-list]`
   192вҶ’Contains items and groups. Animate height using the `--cmdk-list-height` CSS variable.
   193вҶ’
   194вҶ’```css
   195вҶ’[cmdk-list] {
   196вҶ’  min-height: 300px;
   197вҶ’  height: var(--cmdk-list-height);
   198вҶ’  max-height: 500px;
   199вҶ’  transition: height 100ms ease;
   200вҶ’}
   201вҶ’```
   202вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   212вҶ’### Item `[cmdk-item]` `[data-disabled?]` `[data-selected?]`
   214вҶ’Item that becomes active on pointer enter. You should provide a unique `value` for each item, but it will be automatically inferred from the `.textContent`.
   215вҶ’
   216вҶ’```tsx
   217вҶ’<Command.Item
   218вҶ’  onSelect={(value) => console.log('Selected', value)}
   219вҶ’  // Value is implicity "apple" because of the provided text content
   220вҶ’>
   221вҶ’  Apple
   222вҶ’</Command.Item>
   223вҶ’```
   224вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   242вҶ’### Group `[cmdk-group]` `[hidden?]`
   244вҶ’Groups items together with the given `heading` (`[cmdk-group-heading]`).
   245вҶ’
   246вҶ’```tsx
   247вҶ’<Command.Group heading="Fruit">
   248вҶ’  <Command.Item>Apple</Command.Item>
   249вҶ’</Command.Group>
   250вҶ’```
   251вҶ’
   252вҶ’Groups will not unmount from the DOM, rather the `hidden` attribute is applied to hide it from view. This may be relevant in your styling.
   253вҶ’
   254вҶ’You can force a group to always render, regardless of filtering, by passing the `forceMount` prop.
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   256вҶ’### Separator `[cmdk-separator]`
   258вҶ’Visible when the search query is empty or `alwaysRender` is true, hidden otherwise.
   259вҶ’
   260вҶ’### Empty `[cmdk-empty]`
   262вҶ’Automatically renders when there are no results for the search query.
   263вҶ’
   264вҶ’### Loading `[cmdk-loading]`
   266вҶ’You should conditionally render this with `progress` while loading asynchronous items.
   267вҶ’
   268вҶ’```tsx
   269вҶ’const [loading, setLoading] = React.useState(false)
   270вҶ’
   271вҶ’return <Command.List>{loading && <Command.Loading>Hang onвҖҰ</Command.Loading>}</Command.List>
   272вҶ’```
   273вҶ’
   274вҶ’### `useCommandState(state => state.selectedField)`
   276вҶ’Hook that composes [`useSyncExternalStore`](https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-reference.html#usesyncexternalstore). Pass a function that returns a slice of the command menu state to re-render when that slice changes. This hook is provided for advanced use cases and should not be commonly used.
   277вҶ’
   278вҶ’A good use case would be to render a more detailed empty state, like so:
   279вҶ’
   280вҶ’```tsx
   281вҶ’const search = useCommandState((state) => state.search)
   282вҶ’return <Command.Empty>No results found for "{search}".</Command.Empty>
   283вҶ’```
   284вҶ’
   285вҶ’## Examples
   287вҶ’Code snippets for common use cases.
   288вҶ’
   289вҶ’### Nested items
   291вҶ’Often selecting one item should navigate deeper, with a more refined set of items. For example selecting "Change themeвҖҰ" should show new items "Dark theme" and "Light theme". We call these sets of items "pages", and they can be implemented with simple state:
   292вҶ’
   293вҶ’```tsx
   294вҶ’const ref = React.useRef(null)
   295вҶ’const [open, setOpen] = React.useState(false)
   296вҶ’const [search, setSearch] = React.useState('')
   297вҶ’const [pages, setPages] = React.useState([])
   298вҶ’const page = pages[pages.length - 1]
   299вҶ’
   300вҶ’return (
   301вҶ’  <Command
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   338вҶ’### Show sub-items when searching
   340вҶ’If your items have nested sub-items that you only want to reveal when searching, render based on the search state:
   341вҶ’
   342вҶ’```tsx
   343вҶ’const SubItem = (props) => {
   344вҶ’  const search = useCommandState((state) => state.search)
   345вҶ’  if (!search) return null
   346вҶ’  return <Command.Item {...props} />
   347вҶ’}
   348вҶ’
   349вҶ’return (
   350вҶ’  <Command>
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   361вҶ’### Asynchronous results
   363вҶ’Render the items as they become available. Filtering and sorting will happen automatically.
   364вҶ’
   365вҶ’```tsx
   366вҶ’const [loading, setLoading] = React.useState(false)
   367вҶ’const [items, setItems] = React.useState([])
   368вҶ’
   369вҶ’React.useEffect(() => {
   370вҶ’  async function getItems() {
   371вҶ’    setLoading(true)
   372вҶ’    const res = await api.get('/dictionary')
   373вҶ’    setItems(res)
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   397вҶ’### Use inside Popover
   399вҶ’We recommend using the [Radix UI popover](https://www.radix-ui.com/docs/primitives/components/popover) component. вҢҳK relies on the Radix UI Dialog component, so this will reduce your bundle size a bit due to shared dependencies.
   400вҶ’
   401вҶ’```bash
   402вҶ’$ pnpm install @radix-ui/react-popover
   403вҶ’```
   404вҶ’
   405вҶ’Render `Command` inside of the popover content:
   406вҶ’
   407вҶ’```tsx
   408вҶ’import * as Popover from '@radix-ui/react-popover'
   409вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   426вҶ’### Drop in stylesheets
   428вҶ’You can find global stylesheets to drop in as a starting point for styling. See [website/styles/cmdk](website/styles/cmdk) for examples.
   429вҶ’
   430вҶ’## FAQ
   432вҶ’**Accessible?** Yes. Labeling, aria attributes, and DOM ordering tested with Voice Over and Chrome DevTools. [Dialog](#dialog-cmdk-dialog-cmdk-overlay) composes an accessible Dialog implementation.
   433вҶ’
   434вҶ’**Virtualization?** No. Good performance up to 2,000-3,000 items, though. Read below to bring your own.
   435вҶ’
   436вҶ’**Filter/sort items manually?** Yes. Pass `shouldFilter={false}` to [Command](#command-cmdk-root). Better memory usage and performance. Bring your own virtualization this way.
   437вҶ’
   438вҶ’**React 18 safe?** Yes, required. Uses React 18 hooks like `useId` and `useSyncExternalStore`.
   439вҶ’
   440вҶ’**Unstyled?** Yes, use the listed CSS selectors.
   441вҶ’
   442вҶ’**Hydration mismatch?** No, likely a bug in your code. Ensure the `open` prop to `Command.Dialog` is `false` on the server.
   443вҶ’
   444вҶ’**React strict mode safe?** Yes. Open an issue if you notice an issue.
   445вҶ’
   446вҶ’**Weird/wrong behavior?** Make sure your `Command.Item` has a `key` and unique `value`.
   447вҶ’
   448вҶ’**Concurrent mode safe?** Maybe, but concurrent mode is not yet real. Uses risky approaches like manual DOM ordering.
   449вҶ’
   450вҶ’**React server component?** No, it's a client component.
   451вҶ’
   452вҶ’**Listen for вҢҳK automatically?** No, do it yourself to have full control over keybind context.
   453вҶ’
   454вҶ’**React Native?** No, and no plans to support it. If you build a React Native version, let us know and we'll link your repository here.
   455вҶ’
   456вҶ’## History
   458вҶ’Written in 2019 by Paco ([@pacocoursey](https://twitter.com/pacocoursey)) to see if a composable combobox API was possible. Used for the Vercel command menu and autocomplete by Rauno ([@raunofreiberg](https://twitter.com/raunofreiberg)) in 2020. Re-written independently in 2022 with a simpler and more performant approach. Ideas and help from Shu ([@shuding\_](https://twitter.com/shuding_)).
   459вҶ’
   460вҶ’[use-descendants](https://github.com/pacocoursey/use-descendants) was extracted from the 2019 version.
   461вҶ’
   462вҶ’## Testing
   464вҶ’First, install dependencies and Playwright browsers:
   465вҶ’
   466вҶ’```bash
   467вҶ’pnpm install
   468вҶ’pnpm playwright install
   469вҶ’```
   470вҶ’
   471вҶ’Then ensure you've built the library:
   472вҶ’
   473вҶ’```bash
   474вҶ’pnpm build
   475вҶ’```
   476вҶ’
   477вҶ’Then run the tests using your local build against real browser engines:
   478вҶ’
   479вҶ’```bash
   480вҶ’pnpm test
   481вҶ’```
cmdk/src/command-score.ts
    54вҶ’function commandScoreInner(
    55вҶ’  string,
    56вҶ’  abbreviation,
    57вҶ’  lowerString,
    58вҶ’  lowerAbbreviation,
    59вҶ’  stringIndex,
    60вҶ’  abbreviationIndex,
    61вҶ’  memoizedResults,
    62вҶ’) {
    63вҶ’  if (abbreviationIndex === abbreviation.length) {
    64вҶ’    if (stringIndex === string.length) {
    65вҶ’      return SCORE_CONTINUE_MATCH
    66вҶ’    }
    67вҶ’    return PENALTY_NOT_COMPLETE
    68вҶ’  }
    69вҶ’
    70вҶ’  var memoizeKey = `${stringIndex},${abbreviationIndex}`
    71вҶ’  if (memoizedResults[memoizeKey] !== undefined) {
    72вҶ’    return memoizedResults[memoizeKey]
    73вҶ’  }
    74вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   150вҶ’function formatInput(string) {
   151вҶ’  // convert all valid space characters to space so they match each other
   152вҶ’  return string.toLowerCase().replace(COUNT_SPACE_REGEXP, ' ')
   153вҶ’}
   155вҶ’export function commandScore(string: string, abbreviation: string, aliases: string[]): number {
   156вҶ’  /* NOTE:
   157вҶ’   * in the original, we used to do the lower-casing on each recursive call, but this meant that toLowerCase()
   158вҶ’   * was the dominating cost in the algorithm, passing both is a little ugly, but considerably faster.
   159вҶ’   */
   160вҶ’  string = aliases && aliases.length > 0 ? `${string + ' ' + aliases.join(' ')}` : string
   161вҶ’  return commandScoreInner(string, abbreviation, formatInput(string), formatInput(abbreviation), 0, 0, {})
   162вҶ’}
