website/README.md
     3вҶ’## Getting Started
     5вҶ’First, run the development server:
     6вҶ’
     7вҶ’```bash
     8вҶ’pnpm run dev
     9вҶ’```
    10вҶ’
    11вҶ’Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) with your browser to see the result.
    12вҶ’
    13вҶ’You can start editing the page by modifying `pages/index.tsx`. The page auto-updates as you edit the file.
    14вҶ’
    15вҶ’[API routes](https://nextjs.org/docs/api-routes/introduction) can be accessed on [http://localhost:3000/api/hello](http://localhost:3000/api/hello). This endpoint can be edited in `pages/api/hello.ts`.
    16вҶ’
    17вҶ’The `pages/api` directory is mapped to `/api/*`. Files in this directory are treated as [API routes](https://nextjs.org/docs/api-routes/introduction) instead of React pages.
    18вҶ’
    19вҶ’## Learn More
    21вҶ’To learn more about Next.js, take a look at the following resources:
    22вҶ’
    23вҶ’- [Next.js Documentation](https://nextjs.org/docs) - learn about Next.js features and API.
    24вҶ’- [Learn Next.js](https://nextjs.org/learn) - an interactive Next.js tutorial.
    25вҶ’
    26вҶ’You can check out [the Next.js GitHub repository](https://github.com/vercel/next.js/) - your feedback and contributions are welcome!
    27вҶ’
    28вҶ’## Deploy on Vercel
    30вҶ’The easiest way to deploy your Next.js app is to use the [Vercel Platform](https://vercel.com/new?utm_medium=default-template&filter=next.js&utm_source=create-next-app&utm_campaign=create-next-app-readme) from the creators of Next.js.
    31вҶ’
    32вҶ’Check out our [Next.js deployment documentation](https://nextjs.org/docs/deployment) for more details.
